definition.value: A thiopurine that is inosine in which the aromatic hydroxy group is replaced by a methylsulfanediyl group.
A mesoporphyrin with an N-methyl substituent at the 22-position.
A (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2S)-2-methyltetradecanoic acid.
An N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminide having a methyl substituent at the anomeric position.
An iminium ion obtained by dimethylation of the imino group of 4-{[4-(dimethylamino)phenyl](phenyl)methylene}cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-imine. Used in the form of its chloride salt as a green-coloured dye.
A mercaptopropanoic acid that is propanoic acid carrying a sulfanyl group at position 3.
A Good's buffer substance, pKa = 7.2 at 20 degreeC.

A carbotricyclic compound that is pleuromutilin in which the hydroxyacetate group is replaced by a 2-{[2-(diethylamino)ethyl]sulfanyl}acetate group. An antibacterial drug, tiamulin is used in veterinary medicine (generally as its hydrogen fumarate salt) for the treatment of swine dysentery caused by Serpulina hyodysenteriae.

A pyrimidone that is uracil which is substituted at positions 1, 5 and 6 by ethoxymethyl, isopropyl, and benzyl groups, respectively. A non-nucleoside inhibitor of HIV-1 reverse transcriptase, emivirine was an unsuccessful experimental agent for the treatment of HIV.
A menaquinone whose side-chain contains 9 isoprene units in an all-trans-configuration.
A methylthio-1,3,5-triazine that is 2-(methylsulfanyl)-1,3,5-triazine substituted by a tert-butylamino and an ethylamino group at positions 2 and 4 respectively.
An organophosphonate oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from the phosphonic acid group of 1-aminocyclopropylphosphonic acid.
An  alkylbenzene that is benzene substituted by a butyl group at position 1.
An optically active form of N-methylvaline having L-configuration.
A glycol that is the (S)-enantiomer of 2-methylpentane-2,4-diol.
A naphthalenesulfonic acid in which the sulfo group is linked to position 2 of the naphthalene ring.
A D-glucosaminide consisting of 2-aminoglucosamine attached to 1D-myo-inositol at the 6-position via an alpha-linkage.
A nicotinamide dinucleotide consisting of NADP zwitterion lacking the 2'-phsopho group and having a (1R)-1-hydroxy-2-oxo-3-phosphonooxypropyl group at position 4 of the nicotinamide fragment.
